    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 MODEL - FAN SYSTEMS - TROUBLESHOOTING</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>TROUBLESHOOTING</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <seqlist style="alphauc">
                <item>
                    <para>Before beginning these test procedures, make sure the vehicle batteries are at 75% state of
                        charge (SOC) or higher. This represents an open circuit voltage (OCV) of 12.4 volts. Batteries
                        with an OCV of 12 volts or less are either completely discharged or have a dead cell.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Before beginning these test procedures, check any light or indicator lamp filaments that are
                        suspected of being open (burned out). This is done to avoid unnecessary extensive circuit
                        checks.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Before beginning these test procedures, inspect all connectors for loose or damaged pins,
                        wires, etc. Refer to TEST EQUIPMENT AND CONNECTOR REPAIR section in GROUP 08 - ELECTRICAL in the
                        CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>When the technician determines that a fuse is blown, while checking its condition, he is
                        directed to locate the cause of the overload condition and to repair it. While no further
                        instruction on this procedure is listed in the diagnostic tables, the common procedure is as
                        follows: isolate sections of the circuit, by disconnecting connectors, and measure the
                        resistance to ground to find the circuit that is shorted to ground. Then locate the damaged spot
                        in the wire or connector and repair.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Diagnostics for circuits that are malfunctioning by sticking in the on position are generally
                        not covered in detail. It is assumed that the technician knows to check for a malfunctioning
                        switch, relay, or solenoid.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Horton Fan With Cummins M11 or N14 With or Without Air Conditioning</title>
            <table id="t0827501" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Horton Fan With Cummins M11 or N14 With or Without Air Conditioning</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.61in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.64in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.81in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.90in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.67in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.43in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect ECM connector (263) and A/C pressure switch connector (240). Measure
                                    resistance from (263) circuit 97-G to (240) circuit 23-GB.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(263), 97-G to (240), 23-GB.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97-G or 23-GB.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Does vehicle have air conditioning?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to Step 4.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At (240) measure resistance across black wires of A/C pressure switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Switch (240), black wire to black wire.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to Step 5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace defective A/C pressure switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At (240) measure resistance from black wire to black wire of A/C pressure switch
                                    jumper plug.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Jumper plug (240), black wire to black wire.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace defective A/C jumper plug.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect Cummins engine connector (309) and measure resistance from cavity T to
                                    connector (240) circuit 23C.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(309), cavity T to (240), 23C.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 23C, conn. (309) or air conditioning
                                    input circuit, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Reconnect connector (309) and (240), disconnect connector (239), and start engine.
                                    <emph type="bold">WARNING: Fan will be rotating.</emph>
                                    At connector (239) and circuit 23D, measure voltage to ground.
                                    <emph type="bold">NOTE: Engine must be cool and when applicable, A/C should be
                                        turned off.
                                    </emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(239), 23D to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in fan clutch driver circuit, or circuit 23D
                                    from engine connector (309) terminal C, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>With engine still running and relatively cool, at connector (239), measure voltage
                                    from circuit 23D to 23-GA.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(239), 23D to 23-GA.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 23-GA or 11-GU (11-GH with M11), then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>With engine still running and relatively cool, reconnect fan solenoid connector
                                    (239). Does fan slow or stop rotating?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Replace defective fan solenoid.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>9.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Shut off engine. Fan circuits check good. If fan fails to function properly, check
                                    ECM programming and A/C pressure switch opening pressure.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcproc>
